{"batch":"mid_level_elegance","batch_index":5,"assessments":{"mid_level_elegance":67.0},"dimension_notes":{"mid_level_elegance":{"evidence":["The play-by-play to possession translation is reimplemented separately in `step2_build_possessions.py`, `build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py`, `categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py`, `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py`, and `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py`, each rebuilding team extraction, possession grouping, and defensive-foul filtering instead of handing off through one shared seam.","The season scripts expose different intermediate contracts for the same concept: `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` returns a per-possession DataFrame with `L_t/F_t/N_t/M_t`, while `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` skips that layer and returns a tuple of aggregate counts from raw actions, so cross-script changes require understanding multiple incompatible boundary shapes.","Failure propagation is not predictable across these orchestration paths: `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` converts exhausted retries into `{\"status\": \"missing\"}` even after transient 403/429/5xx handling, while `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` catches all exceptions around `future.result()` and only accumulates opaque `failed_ids`, leaving callers with different meanings for the same failure categories."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"}},"issues":[{"dimension":"mid_level_elegance","identifier":"duplicated_pbp_to_possession_seam","summary":"Multiple scripts duplicate the same play-by-play to possession boundary logic instead of sharing one seam.","related_files":["build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py","step2_build_possessions.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["`build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py:69-150` normalizes actions, derives `possession_group`, filters defensive fouls, and computes `L_t/F_t/N_t/M_t` inside the script.","`categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py:72-168` repeats the same normalization and possession grouping but builds a different event-level table.","`step2_build_possessions.py:38-128` repeats normalization and possession grouping again for a possession export.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py:42-100` implements another private possession-table builder, and `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py:88-153` rebuilds the same seam as a foul vector instead of calling a shared translator."],"suggestion":"Extract a single production module for play-by-play normalization and possession summarization, with one explicit output model such as `NormalizedGame` or `PossessionTable`. Have the game-level and season-level scripts call that module and keep only final formatting/reporting in the scripts.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"missing_shared_boundary_layer"},{"dimension":"mid_level_elegance","identifier":"incompatible_wmi_pipeline_contracts","summary":"The WMI pipeline changes shape between scripts, so there is no single obvious handoff from possession data to aggregation.","related_files":["build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawgame_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["`build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py:152-165` emits a CSV-oriented possession model table including `L_t`, `F_t`, `N_t`, and `M_t`.","`calculate_wmi_rawgame_okc_mil.py:47-55` consumes only `L_t/F_t/N_t` from that table and recomputes `M_t`, so the producer/consumer contract is already partially duplicated.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py:100-190` uses a per-game DataFrame seam similar to the single-game path, but `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py:132-174` skips that seam and returns raw aggregate tuples `(n1, n0, sum_m_l1, sum_m_l0)` from `actions`.","Because each layer hands off a different representation for the same metric pipeline, a formula or filtering change must be propagated manually through several boundary shapes."],"suggestion":"Define one canonical handoff for WMI inputs, for example a possession-level record schema or a small typed result object, and make both single-game and season aggregators consume that same contract. Keep derived formulas like `M_t` in one layer only.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"missing_shared_boundary_layer"},{"dimension":"mid_level_elegance","identifier":"inconsistent_failure_protocols_between_runners","summary":"Related orchestration paths report fetch and parse failures with different meanings, which makes integration behavior hard to predict.","related_files":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py"],"evidence":["`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py:69-85` retries 403/404/429/5xx responses and then returns `(\"missing\", None)` when retries are exhausted, collapsing transport trouble and truly absent games into the same downstream status.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py:156-174` maps those outcomes into `status` values `ok`, `missing`, and `error`, but only `game_wmi_components` failures become `error`.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py:128-154` catches every exception from `future.result()` and records only a game id in `failed_ids`, with no reason code, then retries those ids later through a second path.","A caller or maintainer cannot rely on one consistent failure contract across the two season runners, even though both are performing the same integration with the NBA play-by-play feed."],"suggestion":"Introduce a shared fetch/result type for season processing with explicit categories such as `ok`, `missing_game`, `transient_fetch_failure`, and `invalid_payload`, and make both season scripts propagate those categories unchanged through retries and summary reporting.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"missing_shared_boundary_layer"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["The project is organized as standalone analytical scripts, so each new script rebuilds its own integration layer instead of depending on a shared translator.","There is no canonical intermediate model for possession-level WMI inputs, so adjacent layers invent their own handoff formats.","Retry and status handling were added locally per script rather than defined once for the NBA API boundary."],"likely_symptoms":["duplicated_pbp_to_possession_seam","incompatible_wmi_pipeline_contracts","inconsistent_failure_protocols_between_runners"],"possible_false_positives":["Some repeated parsing code may also look like low_level_elegance duplication, but the primary problem here is inconsistent cross-script seams and handoffs."]}}
